dataIdInfo.idAbs: DCP Mapping Lots includes features that are not on the Tax Map. They have been added and maintained by DCP for cartographic purpose. There are three kinds of Mapping Lots: street center 'malls' which are small road-divider type blocks separating lanes of traffic on certain streets; Traffic islands which are small traffic lane separators or pedestrian rest stop blocks other than malls (usually at intersections); streets through parks which are streets existing physically in parks but are not part of the Tax Map.
